article.headline: Hawaii 48, Fresno State 46
article.story:
FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Jade Abele hit a layup with two seconds
left on the clock to lift Hawaii to a 48-46 victory over Fresno
State on Saturday in the Western Athletic Conference opener for
both teams.

The Rainbow Wahine (3-7) took a 44-40 lead on back-to-back
baskets by April Atuaia. Fresno State (6-5) then went on a 6-2 run,
capped by a turnaround jumper by Aritta Lane, to tie the score at
46-46.

Abele ended with a game-high 15 points and led Hawaii with nine
rebounds.

Senior Chanie Sutherland had a career-high 14 points for the
Bulldogs. Teammate Mindy Clark grabbed 14 rebounds to go along with
10 points.

Hawaii was to continue its road trip Monday at Nevada before
winding it up Thursday at San Jose State.
